===Pronunciation===
*Rhymes: [[Rhymes:English:-ɪki|-ɪki]]

===Noun===
'''hickey''' (''plural:'' '''hickeys''')

#(''US slang'') A [[bruise]]-like mark made during [[love-making]] by pressing the mouth to the skin on one’s partner’s body and sucking.
#Used by some speakers to refer to an object whose name is unknown or cannot be recalled.
#<!-- printers' jargon? -->A printing defect <!-- in offset at least and probably also in letterpress -->resembling ''1'' caused by foreign matter on the printing surface<!-- such as the litho plate --> resulting in a ring where the ink is missing.

====Synonyms====
*(''bruise-like mark''): [[love bite]]

